  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And this was known to all",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] It is better to render, with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Rev. Ver.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the verb literally, “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "became",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "known",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” It was no doubt a gradual spreading of the story. We may be sure that the “sons of Sceva” said little about it.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Jews and Greeks also dwelling at Ephesus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "both Jews and Greeks, that dwelt at Ephesus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The A. V. does not shew “Jews and Greeks” to be an explanation of the preceding “all,” which it is in the original. Exorcists were plentiful enough at Ephesus, and the event would be looked on as a warning.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and fear … magnified",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The “fear” was the first feeling and the most widely prevailing, for that would touch all who heard the history; the magnifying of the Lord Jesus was the later effect produced among those to whom Jesus was becoming known and worshipped.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἐμεγαλύντεο",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was magnified",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") These exorcists were treated more severely than that person, who was casting out demons in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 9:49-50",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". But the same persons, though not forbidden by Paul, yet by the very disaster which they suffered were ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the Christian cause (in spite of themselves). The contumely cast on those who act in a sinister manner is subservient to the Divine glory, and to the estimation of the servants of GOD endowed with real power.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
